-- int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
-- int_deduped_billing: Deduplicate billing events by subscription and month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM billing_events
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- fct_subscription_metrics: Monthly subscription metrics aggregated by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(u.company_id, NULL) AS company_id,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        COALESCE(SUM(be.amount), 0) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM subscriptions s
    LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN dim_companies c ON COALESCE(u.company_id, NULL) = c.company_id
    LEFT JOIN dim_plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN int_deduped_billing be ON s.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
        AND EXTRACT(MONTH FROM be.event_month) = EXTRACT(MONTH FROM s.started_at)
        AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM be.event_month) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM s.started_at)
    WHERE s.status = 'active'
    GROUP BY COALESCE(u.company_id, NULL), c.industry, p.tier
)
SELECT
    event_month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
ORDER BY event_month DESC, active_subscriptions DESC
